<p>The <b>Akhil Bharatiya Akhara Parishad</b> (All India Akhara Council) is the apex organisation of <a href="/wiki/Sikh" title="Sikh">Sikh</a> and <a href="/wiki/Hindu" title="Hindu">Hindu</a> <a href="/wiki/Sant" title="Sant">Sants</a> (saints) and <a href="/wiki/Sadhu" title="Sadhu">Sadhus</a> (ascetics) in <a href="/wiki/India" title="India">India</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-A_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-A-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-D_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-D-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> The ABAP is composed of 14 <i><a href="/wiki/Akhara" title="Akhara">Akharas</a></i>, or organisations of Hindu sants and sadhus. <a href="/wiki/Nirmohi_Akhara" title="Nirmohi Akhara">Nirmohi Akhara</a> (involved in the <a href="/wiki/Ram_Janmabhoomi" title="Ram Janmabhoomi">Ram Janmabhoomi</a> <a href="/wiki/Ayodhya_dispute" title="Ayodhya dispute">dispute</a> in Ayodhya) and <a href="/wiki/Shri_Dattatreya_Akhara" title="Shri Dattatreya Akhara">Shri Dattatreya Akhara</a> are two of the prominent akharas which are part of it.</p>
<p></p>
